chPowerOperationalStatus.name: chPowerOperationalStatus
chPowerOperationalStatus.description: This object reflects the overall status of the chassis's power supply in terms of how the power is being delivered to the chassis.

chPowerMainVoltageStatus.name: chPowerMainVoltageStatus
chPowerMainVoltageStatus.description: This object reflects the state of the main voltage rail within the chassis. The power on this rail may be delivered by AC supplies, DC supplies or battery supplies.

chPowerMainVoltage.name: chPowerMainVoltage
chPowerMainVoltage.description: The voltage of the chassis's main voltage rail. This rail carries power to all the modules in the chassis. It has an allowable range of 40 volts to 60 volts DC. The value of this object is the actual voltage * 10.

chPowerTotalSupply.name: chPowerTotalSupply
chPowerTotalSupply.description: The total power being supplied by the chassis's power supplies to the chassis. The value of this object is the actual watts.

chPowerTotalLoad.name: chPowerTotalLoad
chPowerTotalLoad.description: The total load being presented by the chassis to the chassis's power supplies. The value of this object is the actual watts.

chPowerMaxSupply.name: chPowerMaxSupply
chPowerMaxSupply.description: The maximum power that could de supplied by the chassis's power supplies to the chassis. The value of this object is the actual watts.

chPowerMaxLoad.name: chPowerMaxLoad
chPowerMaxLoad.description: The maximum load that could be presented by the chassis to the chassis's power supplies. The value of this object is the actual watts.

chPowerTable.name: chPowerTable
chPowerTable.description: A list of power lines or busses on the chassis's backplane.

chPowerEntry.name: chPowerEntry
chPowerEntry.description: A slot entry containing objects for a particular module and associated power line.

chPowerLineID.name: chPowerLineID
chPowerLineID.description: A unique value used to identify a particular power line on the chassis's backplane.

chPowerLineType.name: chPowerLineType
chPowerLineType.description: The type of power. For example, a power line that supplies DC current at a nominal voltage of 40 to 57 volts or a power line that supplies AC current at a nominal volatge of 110v.

chPowerLineTotalSupply.name: chPowerLineTotalSupply
chPowerLineTotalSupply.description: The total power being supplied by the chassis's power supplies to the chassis on this power line. The value of this object is the actual watts.

chPowerLineTotalLoad.name: chPowerLineTotalLoad
chPowerLineTotalLoad.description: The total load being presented by the chassis to the chassis's power supplies on this power line. This value will be zero if unknown The value of this object is the actual watts.

chPowerLineMaxSupply.name: chPowerLineMaxSupply
chPowerLineMaxSupply.description: The maximum power that could de supplied by the chassis's power supplies to the chassison this power line. The value of this object is the actual watts.

chPowerLineMaxLoad.name: chPowerLineMaxLoad
chPowerLineMaxLoad.description: The maximum load that could be presented by the chassis to the chassis's power supplies on this power line. The value of this object is the actual watts.

chPowerDiagVoltageStatus.name: chPowerDiagVoltageStatus
chPowerDiagVoltageStatus.description: This object reflects the state of the diag voltage rail within the chassis.

chPowerDiagVoltage.name: chPowerDiagVoltage
chPowerDiagVoltage.description: The voltage of the chassis's diag voltage rail. This rail carries power to all the modules in the chassis. It has an allowable range of 4.75 volts to 5.25 volts DC. The value of this object is the actual voltage * 10.

boardPowerSlotStatusTable.name: boardPowerSlotStatusTable
boardPowerSlotStatusTable.description: A list of networking modules installed in this chassis.

boardPowerSlotStatusEntry.name: boardPowerSlotStatusEntry
boardPowerSlotStatusEntry.description: A slot entry containing objects for a particular module.

boardPowerSlotStatusID.name: boardPowerSlotStatusID
boardPowerSlotStatusID.description: The slot number of a chassis slot in which this board is installed. This object is similiar to chSlotID in the Chassis MIB.

boardPowerOperationalStatus.name: boardPowerOperationalStatus
boardPowerOperationalStatus.description: This object reflects the status of the module's DC-DC converter power supply.

boardPowerAdminStatus.name: boardPowerAdminStatus
boardPowerAdminStatus.description: This object controls the operation of the module's DC-DC power supply. If the value 3 is written to this object then the value of the object will be set to 1 after the reset is performed.

boardPowerLocalAdminStatus.name: boardPowerLocalAdminStatus
boardPowerLocalAdminStatus.description: This object controls the operation of the module's front panel button. In local mode this button may be used to locally control the operation of the DC-DC converter, i.e. power on, power off and reset. In secure mode a request the state of the front panel button is reflected in the object boardPowerOperationalStatus. In secure mode the front panel button has no effect locally.

boardPowerLocalStatus.name: boardPowerLocalStatus
boardPowerLocalStatus.description: This object reflects the state of the module's front panel button.

boardPowerShutdownAdmin.name: boardPowerShutdownAdmin
boardPowerShutdownAdmin.description: This object controls whether or not the module should auto power down due to an fault condition.

boardPowerPriority.name: boardPowerPriority
boardPowerPriority.description: The module's power-up and power down priority. This is a value of 1 to 14 and is used to decide which modules are allowed to power on in the event that power demand of the chassis is greater than the total power supply. The default value is 14, highest priority. When two modules have equal priority then the module in the lowest slot wins.

boardPowerMaxInputPower.name: boardPowerMaxInputPower
boardPowerMaxInputPower.description: The maximum input power that this module is allowed to consume. The value of this object is actual watts.

boardPowerSlotTable.name: boardPowerSlotTable
boardPowerSlotTable.description: A list of networking modules and associated power lines installed in this chassis.

boardPowerSlotEntry.name: boardPowerSlotEntry
boardPowerSlotEntry.description: A slot entry containing objects for a particular module and associated power line.

boardPowerSlotID.name: boardPowerSlotID
boardPowerSlotID.description: The slot number of a chassis slot in which this board is installed. This object is similiar to chSlotID in the Chassis MIB.

boardPowerID.name: boardPowerID
boardPowerID.description: A unique value used to identify a particular power line.

boardPowerType.name: boardPowerType
boardPowerType.description: The type of power. For example, a power line that supplies DC current at a nominal voltage of 40 to 57 volts or a power line that supplies AC current at a nominal volatge of 110v.

boardPowerStatus.name: boardPowerStatus
boardPowerStatus.description: This object reflects the status of this power line.

boardPowerVoltage.name: boardPowerVoltage
boardPowerVoltage.description: The voltage reading for the power line. The value of this object is actual voltage * 100.

boardPowerCurrent.name: boardPowerCurrent
boardPowerCurrent.description: The current reading for the power line. The value of this object is the actual amperage * 100. If this reading is not implemented then value will be zero.

boardPowerMaxVoltage.name: boardPowerMaxVoltage
boardPowerMaxVoltage.description: The maximum voltage for this power line. If the voltage reading for this power line is greater than this value then the power line is considered to be in an overvolatge condition. The value of this object is in voltage * 100.

boardPowerMinVoltage.name: boardPowerMinVoltage
boardPowerMinVoltage.description: The minimum voltage for this power line. If the voltage reading for this power line is less than this value then the power line is considered to be in an undervolatge condition. The value of this object is voltage * 100.

boardPowerMaxPower.name: boardPowerMaxPower
boardPowerMaxPower.description: The maximum power for this power line. If the power calculated for this power line is greater than this value then the power line is considered to be in an overload condition. The value of this object is in watts.

psPowerSlotStatusTable.name: psPowerSlotStatusTable
psPowerSlotStatusTable.description: A list of AC & DC power supplies installed in this chassis.

psPowerSlotStatusEntry.name: psPowerSlotStatusEntry
psPowerSlotStatusEntry.description: A slot entry containing objects for a particular power supply.

psPowerSlotStatusID.name: psPowerSlotStatusID
psPowerSlotStatusID.description: The slot number of a chassis slot in which this AC power supply is installed. This object is similiar to chSlotID in the Chassis MIB.

psPowerOperationalStatus.name: psPowerOperationalStatus
psPowerOperationalStatus.description: This object reflects the status of the module's DC-DC converter power supply.

psPowerAdminStatus.name: psPowerAdminStatus
psPowerAdminStatus.description: This object controls the operation of power supply.

psPowerMaxOutputPower.name: psPowerMaxOutputPower
psPowerMaxOutputPower.description: The maximum power that this power supply is allowed to ouput. The value of this object is watts.

psPowerSlotTable.name: psPowerSlotTable
psPowerSlotTable.description: A list of power supplies and associated power lines installed in this chassis.

psPowerSlotEntry.name: psPowerSlotEntry
psPowerSlotEntry.description: A slot entry containing objects for a particular power line on a particular power supply.

psPowerSlotID.name: psPowerSlotID
psPowerSlotID.description: The slot number of a chassis slot in which this Power supply is installed. This object is similiar to chSlotID in the Chassis MIB.

psPowerID.name: psPowerID
psPowerID.description: A unique value used to identify a particular power line.

psPowerType.name: psPowerType
psPowerType.description: The type of power. For example, a power line that supplies DC current at a nominal voltage of 40 to 57 volts or a power line that supplies AC current at a nominal volatge of 110v.

psPowerStatus.name: psPowerStatus
psPowerStatus.description: This object reflects the status of the power line.

psPowerAdmin.name: psPowerAdmin
psPowerAdmin.description: This object controls the operation of power supply.

psPowerVoltage.name: psPowerVoltage
psPowerVoltage.description: The voltage reading for the power line. The value of this object is the actual voltage * 100.

psPowerCurrent.name: psPowerCurrent
psPowerCurrent.description: The current reading for the power line. The value of this object is amperage * 100. If this reading is not implemented then value will be zero.

psPowerLineFrequency.name: psPowerLineFrequency
psPowerLineFrequency.description: The line frequency for the power line. The value of this object is the actual frequency in Hertz * 10. If this reading is not implemented then value will be zero.

psPowerMaxVoltage.name: psPowerMaxVoltage
psPowerMaxVoltage.description: The maximum voltage for this power line. If the voltage reading for this power line is greater than this value then the power line is considered to be in an over volatge condition. The value of this object is voltage * 100.

psPowerMinVoltage.name: psPowerMinVoltage
psPowerMinVoltage.description: The minimum voltage for this power line. If the voltage reading for this power line is greater than this value then the power line is considered to be in an over volatge condition. The value of this object is voltage * 100.

psPowerMaxPower.name: psPowerMaxPower
psPowerMaxPower.description: The maximum power for this power line. If the power calculated for this power line is greater than this value then the power line is considered to be in an overload condition. The value of this object is watts.

termPowerStatus.name: termPowerStatus
termPowerStatus.description: This object reflects the status of the chassis's termination voltage rail.

termPowerVoltage.name: termPowerVoltage
termPowerVoltage.description: The voltage of the chassis's termination voltage rail. This rail carries power to INB terminator cards in the chassis. It has an allowalble range of 3.3 Volt + or - 5%.The value of this object is voltage * 100.

termPowerCurrent.name: termPowerCurrent
termPowerCurrent.description: The current on the chassis's termination voltage rail. The value of this object is the actual amperage * 100. If this reading is not implemented then the value will be zero.

termPowerModule1Status.name: termPowerModule1Status
termPowerModule1Status.description: This object reflects the state of the INB termination module number 1. A value of normal(1) reflects that both busses are normal. A value of fault(4) reflects that both busses are in a fault condition.

termPowerModule2Status.name: termPowerModule2Status
termPowerModule2Status.description: This object reflects the state of the INB termination module number 2. A value of normal(1) reflects that both busses are normal. A value of fault(4) reflects that both busses are in a fault condition.
